meanings.definition: To block or fill up a space to prevent movement.
meanings.sent1: She chocked the door with a chair to keep it closed.
meanings.sent2: The parking lot was chocked with cars during rush hour.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel chocked its cheeks full of nuts for the winter.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter chocked the room, filling it with joy.
meanings.sent5: The dam chocked the river, halting its flow.

meanings.definition: To be completely full or crowded.
meanings.sent1: The movie theater was chocked with excited moviegoers.
meanings.sent2: After the party, the trash can was chocked with empty cups.
meanings.sent3: The refrigerator was chocked with delicious leftovers.
meanings.sent4: Her heart chocked with emotion as she watched the sunset.
meanings.sent5: The highway was chocked with cars during the holiday weekend.

meanings.definition: To stop or prevent something from moving forward.
meanings.sent1: The fallen tree chocked the path, blocking their way.
meanings.sent2: The traffic jam chocked the progress of the delivery truck.
meanings.sent3: The stubborn jar lid chocked her efforts to open it.
meanings.sent4: His fear chocked his ability to speak in front of the crowd.
meanings.sent5: The heavy snow chocked the train tracks, delaying the train.
